                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.05/183: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-27T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 27, 1929—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>389. Your 1005, November 18, 6 p.m. Department believes that in appeals under
                    Article V of Rendition Agreement, Consul is clearly entitled to rights set forth
                    in Article IV of Sino-American Treaty of 1880,<note n="13" xml:id="d721fn13"
                        >Signed at Peking, November 17, 1880; Malloy, <hi rend="italic"
                            >Treaties</hi>, 1776–1909, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p.
                        239.</note> including examination of witnesses. In the light of the
                    information given, however, Department believes that it would be preferable to
                    rely on the rendition agreement rather than <pb facs="0865" n="721"
                        xml:id="pg_721"/> on the treaty and that present difficulty may best be
                    overcome either by endeavoring to have cases returned to Provisional Court for
                    retrial before a different judge and consular officer or by designating a
                    different consular representative in appeal court.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
